<dl id="n25071d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25071d">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25071d"> 71(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> action</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">We could not take that way without destruction, so the generals who had collected together near the Hougoumont hedge dispersed across the fields. General Foy alone remained with the 300 men whom he had gleaned from the field of battle, and marched at their head. Our anxiety was to withdraw from the scene of <mark>action</mark> without being confounded with the fugitives. <small> Edward Creasy, <a name="ECFD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECFD"><cite title="source">The Fifteen Decisive Battles of the World</cite></a> (1915) 439</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14042g" href="c14all.htm#c14042g">VI.C.14:042(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
